Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to
the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Peel and
grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the
@mature cheddar cheese{60%g}(grated).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil for cooking{1%tbsp} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat the oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{60%g} until it starts to brown, ~{1-2%minutes} -
don't let it take on too much colour.

Once browned, transfer the chorizo and carefully drain its oil into a #small bowl{}
with the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g}. Season with @ground black pepper{}, stir to
combine, then set the chorizo crumb aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large frying pan on medium-high heat. Once hot, add
the @diced British chicken thigh{260%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}. Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn
occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

== Roux and Cheese Sauce ==

Melt the @butter{20%g} into the chicken pan on medium-high heat. Once hot, stir
in the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp}. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've
made a roux!

Gradually stir in the @water for the sauce{200%ml}, followed by the
@chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat. Add the cheddar
cheese and stir until melted. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

== Assembly ==

Add the cooked pasta to the cheese sauce and stir to combine. Add a splash of
water to loosen if needed, then transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle the
chorizo crumb evenly over the top.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the crumbs are golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove from your oven and leave to stand.

== Garlicky Tenderstem® Broccoli ==

Meanwhile, clean your frying pan and pop it back on medium-high heat with a
drizzle of oil. Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} stems lengthways.

Once hot, add the broccoli and stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the garlic and
fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Lower
the heat to medium and allow to cook until the broccoli is tender,
~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Spoon the baked penne into #bowls{} and serve the broccoli alongside.

Enjoy!